field.value:
Line #192 in SmtpSender.cs creates an attachment from a stream. It is using an incorrect overload for the constructor and as a consequence is assigning the media type as the file name.

if (attachment.Stream != null)
{
    mailAttach = new Attachment(attachment.Stream, attachment.MediaType);
}

Correct code should be:

if (attachment.Stream != null)
{
    mailAttach = new Attachment(attachment.Stream, attachment.FileName, attachment.MediaType);
}

I do have some tests to display this issue but wasn't sure where to put them (There doesn't appear to be any tests currently for the EmailSender). The tests also require CreateMailMessage to be made public (which is another open issue it seems: COMP-ISSUE-74)
